To enter giveaway:

✔ Simply follow Sprinkles (@sprinklescupcakes) and Lizzy (@lizzymathis) on Instagram
✔ like this video
✔ comment below your Halloween costume or your plans to celebrate Halloween this year

Sprinkles will select 2 winners to each win a Halloween DYO-TO-GO Kit. Giveaway ends on Friday 10/30 at 11:59pm. We will contact winners through direct message. You must live near a Sprinkles bakery to win, as we do not ship our kits. Additionally, winners must pick-up their prize as delivery is not included.

Cashmere Nicole (@cakeandcashmere) is a mom, black-woman business owner & entrepreneur, founder of Beauty Bakerie (@beautybakeriemakeup), and breast cancer survivor. We are proud to partner with her to not only amplify her voice, but to also raise money for @nbcf 🙌

With each purchase of Sprinkles NEW! Beauty Bakerie Honey Lavender & Raspberry cupcake purchased through 10/18, Sprinkles will donate $0.50 to NBCF. Additionally, Beauty Bakerie will donate a portion of proceeds from sales, also through 10/18, from their Milk & Honey Highlighting Palette to NBCF.

node.text:
Exercise your right to #vote!

We are proud to team up with @candaceparker to celebrate #WomensEqualityDay. We believe all women should share their voice and fiercely exercise their right to vote. We not only celebrate this day, but also the 100th Anniversary of the 19th Amendment and the 55th Anniversary of the Voting Rights Act, which gave all women, including women of color, the right to vote. 
 
To honor this occasion, we are baking up a limited-edition Candace Parker Sprinkle Cupcake that is inspired by Candace’s passion for history and the suffragette movement, available 8/24-8/26. $1 for each limited-edition cupcake sold will be donated to vote.org (@votedotorg). This organization uses technology to simplify political engagement, increase voter turnout, and strengthen American democracy.

Now we challenge you to share what HER vote means to you and we’ll select winners to receive these sweet treats!
